Program Overview
This project is a Java-based Payroll System that reads employee information and attendance records from the text files.
The main goal is to automate payroll computation while using file-based storage that is compatible with a handfile
reader. Employee data is converted and stored in a text format so it can be easily read and processed by the system.

User Roles and Features
Employees can:
Log in using their Employee Number
View their salary details, including hours worked, gross salary, deductions, and net salary
Payroll Staff can:
Process payroll for a single employee
Process payroll for all employees

Payroll Computation
For each employee, the system computes:
Total hours worked
Gross salary
Deductions: SSS, PhilHealth, Pag-IBIG, Tax
Net salary

File Handling
All data is read from text files using FileReader and BufferedReader. This approach allows the system to work with
external files generated or accessed by a handfile reader.

